<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3974770>
    dc:description "FIG. 1. a. Gonorynchus abbreviatus, KAUM-I 53441, 68.0 mm SL; Japan: Kagoshima: Kawajiri (photograph by H. Motomura); b, Aperioptus pictorius, about 65 mm SL, from Richardson (1848: pl. 10 fig. 4); c, Acanthopsoides molobrion, CMK 21740, 44.0 mm SL; Borneo: Mahakam drainage; d, mouth of Ap. pictorius, from Richardson (1848: pl. 10 fig. 5). Vertical lines show the position of the origin of the pelvic, dorsal and anal-fin origins, and of the base of the last dorsal-fin ray." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3974770/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

